---
import { PODCAST } from '../../consts';
---

<section id="about" class="section section--panel about">
  <div class="about__row">
    <div class="about__panel">
      <p class="section__label">My story</p>
      <h2 class="about__tagline">It always starts with a question.</h2>
      <div class="about__body">
        <p>
          My first job in tech was as a Technical Productivity Consultant,
          providing off-the-shelf software support to Fortune 500 companies. I
          helped people get more out of Excel and other everyday applications,
          often with no screen to look at, so all I could do was ask the right
          questions until I really understood how things worked. Everything
          I've learned since, I've learned that way.
        </p>
        <p>
          From there I moved into medical devices, leading the rollout and
          training of complex systems in hospitals, coordinating multiple
          departments to ensure smooth adoption and usage in environments
          that never slow down. No two hospitals ran the same way, so I broke
          every installation down, customer by customer, distilling it into
          terms their teams understood to set it up for success in the field.
          All the while, I was streamlining and automating our own internal
          processes to cut out the long, tedious work.
        </p>
        <p>
          Now I'm on the engineering side, building those systems instead of
          rolling them out. And I approach code the same way: figure out what's
          actually needed, build that, and leave the rest out.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm the same way at home, automating anything and everything. And my
          favorite fixes remove steps instead of adding options. Mostly, I just 
          like solving hard problems and helping people do their work better.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about__panel">
      <p class="section__label">What I do</p>
      <h2 class="about__tagline">
        I break things down to solve, to simplify, and to teach.
      </h2>
      <ul class="about__cards">
        <li class="about__card">
          <h3>Solve</h3>
          <p>
            Whether it's professional software for a medical device or one of
            my hobby projects, the approach is the same: understand the whole
            system, then break the problem into manageable pieces.
          </p>
          <a class="about__card-link" href="#projects">See my work &rarr;</a>
        </li>
        <li class="about__card">
          <h3>Simplify</h3>
          <p>
            Breaking down complex processes and workflows to trim the
            unnecessary and automate what's left, from manufacturing and test
            processes to internal tools. The best fix usually leaves less in
            the way.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="about__card">
          <h3>Teach</h3>
          <p>
            Complex topics, sliced into digestible pieces, first to learn,
            then to teach. That's the idea behind <strong>8minute.ai</strong>, my
            podcast helping everyday people make sense of AI. At home, it's
            whatever my kids are curious about.
          </p>
          <a class="about__card-link" href={PODCAST.url} rel="noopener">
            Listen &rarr;
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* The two blocks are separate bordered panels sitting side by side, so this
     section skips the usual single `.container` panel and lays its own pair
     out at the wide width. The story gets the larger reading column. */
  .about__row {
    max-width: var(--wide-width);
    margin-inline: auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 7fr) minmax(0, 5fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  .about__panel {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: var(--space-12) var(--space-8);
  }

  /* Tagline headings are full sentences, so they run a bit smaller than
     section h2s and balance their wrap instead of leaving a one-word line. */
  .about__tagline {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.4vw, 1.75rem);
    text-wrap: balance;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about__body {
    font-size: 1.08rem;
  }
  .about__body p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .about__body p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .about__cards {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }
  .about__card {
    background: var(--color-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
  }
  .about__card h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .about__card p {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .about__card-link {
    font-weight: 550;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  /* Stack the two panels before the columns get cramped. */
  @media (max-width: 62rem) {
    .about__row {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
